        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=2372&FORUM_ID=2&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=General+Discussions&Topic_Title=Wizards"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> I used to think wizards was the biggest waste of space in eq.  They did less damage then melee in a fight and needed large downtime.  After several patches, aa skills, new spells, something is outta wack.</P><P>I never call for nerfing of any class.  Everytime I get jealous of a class, I end up playing it in the future and i'm glad I kept my mouth shut.  I just can't figure out wizzy power now.  What I mean is, are they too powerful or still not powerful enough, but look powerful now? If they are too powerful compared to other casters, are they where casters should be to keep up with melee?</P><P>What brought about this questioning was the other night in on a mini kedge raid. I had my rogue there (58 with crit hit aa ability).  There was a 60 wizzy with crit blast aa also.  The wizards damage output was INSANE.  In our fight with phinny, he got 2 critical blasts of 3400!!!!  Thats like 7000 damage in the span of 10 sec max.  I would think it was a fluke, but I saw critical blasts like that every fight just about.  I was sitting there with my rogue,who usually i'm impressed with, and thinking how insane the damage output of the wizard was.  </P><P>I believe that a wizard and rogue should do similar damage in a fight.  Wizzy more in a short fight, rogue more over a longer fight.  2 rogues couldn't do the damage that the wizzy was putting out.  There is no way in hell my rogue was anywhere near the wizards damage output.  </P><P>I know this sounds like nerf wizards, but I like I said, is this wizard power just LOOK like a lot of damage or are they really doing this much?  You think a solo wizzy should outdamage a 58 rogue, 60 warr and 60 sk?  Well he did on every fight.  Granted he had c3, but we all had haste.   In a long fight with a mob who had 100,000+ hps, it might even out, but whats up.  </P><P>I always hated wizzys in an exp group and still do for some reason. On raids though, most mobs go down FAST and wizzys just rule raids.  With thier lure nukes and 3400+ critical blasts, is the class overbalanced now?  I won't even get into manaburn.  Where is a rogues mana/life burn aa?  Rogues are the melee wizards.  I don't know what I wrote this for, just blown away by the wizards damage.</P><P></P><P> </font></td>

