        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> "3400+ critical blasts, is the class overbalanced now? "</P><P>I dont think so.  Wizards SHOULD be the masters of pure magic damage.  And we aren't talking about a level 52 Wizard here.  We are talking about a level 60 character with massive AA points, relatively rare spells, and likely buffs/focus to reach this kind of damage.  This is a powerful Wizard, and rightfully so.</P><P>I think the problem is not that they are so overbalanced, is that Necros are - underbalanced (but getting better).</P><P>Class envy is really not productive.  The big problem with Necros was the class envy crybabies that wet their diapers every time they saw us solo something.  As Necros, let's not go down that route with other classes, let's focus on improving our own class, it's far more productive.</P><P>Xuraz Xorthexia - <BR>59 Necromancer <BR>Xegony Server<BR>Profile - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=72377" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=72377</a></P><P>Edited by - Xuraz on 04/04/2002  16:37:46<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
