        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> A wizard with Fury and Fury Mastery (36 points total) will have a ~13% chance to crit. That is not a reliable way to deal damage. Besides, the only way to crit for 3400 is via either Sunstrike (1615) or Elnerick's Electrical Rending (rend2.. 1890). Mind you that SS costs 450 mana to cast, and rend2 costs 525. And guess where those spells drop off of? SS only drops off of Talendor, Gore, Sev, Trak, Emperor in seb, VP, very rare spell too, i have never seen one drop to this date. And on innoruuk this spell sells for 10k+, and i rarely see anybody selling it (For example, i have seen 1 person offer a hiero cloak and 8k for this spell now for months, still does not have the spell.). Rend2? Off of the THO, and guess what? Instead of being on the spell loot table, this spell is on the regular loot table making it even rarer. </P><P>So, now ask yourself this, is it fair to nerf the people who actually have those spells? Either getting it by buying it or earning it from a raid. Further more, is it fair to nerf those people with those spells that spent 36 ability points <b>JUST</b> to get those kind of crits?</P><P>My answer is no. If the person is willing to lvl a class to 60. Pay assloads or earn the spells needed to do this much damage. Spend the time leveling up. Get good enough gear to cast those spells multiple times. And finally spending points on skills <b>just</b> to do that kind of damage ... then why nerf them? They put up with so many blocks in the  way, so they deserve a nice reward.</P><P>And sense you are comparing to a rogue, what would you do one day if somebody saw you double critting for 2k+ damage on 2 bs attempts? OMG thats like 8k damage! I gotta make a post about this so rogues who earned the uber weapons needed to crit for 2k+ and spent the points to crit like this nerfed!</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade i