izard again though, and i actually started a new one because i am curious to see if these changes have affected our groupability.</P><P>Necromancers seem to have the opposite problem, powerful and versatile at first and ending as mana batteries.  I think that is pretty damn unfair, and that dot stacking needs to be implemented, along with a pet fix.  It is RIDICULOUS to force damage casters (mages, necros) into utility roles in the endgame when they should be at the culmination of their power.  I think the recent changes in VI to the live team bodes well that these issues will be resolved soon.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>There was a 60 wizzy with crit blast aa also. The wizards damage output was INSANE. In our fight with phinny, he got 2 critical blasts of 3400!!!! Thats like 7000 damage in the span of 10 sec max. I would think it was a fluke, but I saw critical blasts like that every fight just about<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>If you saw crits like that every fight, that wizzie must have been having a REAL good night with the RNG, because crits max at a pretty low percentage.  The innate crits are quite rare, and really have next to no effect on our DPS.  They were added in as a "neat thing for wizards."  As in, something to make a group ooh and aah instead of saying, "don't get a wizard, they just sit there doing nothing!"</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>But..I feel AOE groups trivialize leveling and AA exp. I hang out in Sebilis nowadays because I need 58+ spells. It's damn depressing when so much of the zone is camped by two groups. =/<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>AE groups only LOOK like they trivialize xp because you get all the xp messages at once.  Log parsing indicates that AA groups give about the same xp over time as a holy trinity group once you factor in the long med and repop time.  The whole zone being camped by two groups?  Well, perhaps VI should design some zones specifically around AE groups, since we have nearly all zones in game designed around standard melee/cleric.  Wizards have very few spell lines.  One of them is already completely useless, a literal waste of spellbook space = anything with Al'Kabor in the name.  Other than AE groups, our PBAE unlimited target spells are only good for clearing greenies wheee.  We have to wait until we get Jyll's (either 53 or 54) to really be effective in an AE group, and you have to find a willing enchanter or two, and enough spawns to sustain your group.  Please don't call for a nerf to this tactic, instead call for more zones to be designed with this tactic in mind.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
