        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> I have this to say.</P><P>Wizards are your int casting friends, read on the Wizard boards for Wizards posting that Necros (and mages) need adjustment.</P><P>The case you are quoting WAS a fluke. The highest percent chance for crits is 13% and that is with LOTS of AA. (36 MINIMUM) So him getting two crits in a fight is unusual.</P><P>I agree with your assessment that rogues and wizards should do similar damage in different timeframes. This is not the case, a similarly AA enhanced well equipped assassin will outdamage anyone in the game (except maybe against baneable mobs).</P><P>Wizards suck in grind groups, my wizard is heavily aa enhanced and she STILL sucks grinding. Sure she can do a lot of dmg in the short run, if she can manage not to get aggro, but then.. well she has to med.</P><P>Complaining about wizards does not speak well for necros. I defy you to find an anti necro post on Graffes, and you will find many pro necro posts. (many by me)</P><P>FK</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
